---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Draconis Systems"
  description="Starter terms template for Draconis Systems services. Requires legal review before production launch."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Terms" }]}
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container card stack">
      <p class="badge">Legal Template - Review Required</p>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p>Effective date placeholder: [DD Month YYYY]</p>

      <h2>1. Services</h2>
      <p>
        Draconis Systems provides custom computer system design, sourcing coordination, assembly, validation, and
        related consulting services as defined in accepted quotes.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Quotes and Payment</h2>
      <p>
        Quotes are valid for a limited period due to component market volatility. Final invoice terms, deposit
        requirements, VAT treatment, and accepted payment methods must be defined in writing.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Lead Times</h2>
      <p>
        Timelines are estimates and may shift due to supplier constraints, shipping delays, or customer-requested scope changes.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Warranty and Support</h2>
      <p>
        Warranty coverage and support windows are defined in the final service agreement. Third-party component warranties
        remain subject to manufacturer terms.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, liability is limited to amounts paid for the applicable service order,
        excluding indirect or consequential damages.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>Jurisdiction placeholder: [England and Wales, United Kingdom].</p>

      <p class="small">This document is a starter template and must be reviewed by a qualified legal adviser.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
